news.title: No relief for Dehradun builder from Uttarakhand HC in land fraud case
news.para: Windlass's counsel said the 72-year-old was undergoing treatment for health complications at Himalayan Hospital in Dehradun, as per court directions.

news.title: Goa: ODPs case another indictment of TCP’s urban planning flaws
news.para: From putting on hold a circular on ODPs for the five villages to virtually striking down the TCP department’s power to unilaterally alter the zoning of private plots through Section 17(2) of the TCP Act, 1974, the courts have emerged as the battleground for Goa’s land politics.

news.title: Brookfield India REIT appoints Keki Mistry as independent director
news.para: The Board of Directors of Brookprop Management Services Pvt Ltd, the manager of Brookfield India Real Estate Trust, has approved the appointment of Keki Minoo Mistry as an additional director under the category of independent director.

news.title: Compass files lawsuit against Zillow over private home listings policy
news.para: In a filing with the U.S. District Court for the Southern District of New York, Compass claims that "Zillow has sought to rely on anticompetitive tactics to protect its monopoly and revenues in violation of the antitrust laws."

news.title: Existing home sales rise in USA in May; mortgage rates still a constraint
news.para: Home sales climbed 0.8% last month to a seasonally adjusted annual rate of 4.03 million units, the National Association of Realtors said on Monday. Economists polled by Reuters had forecast home resales falling to a rate of 3.95 million units.

news.title: Holcim completes $30 billion North American spin-off
news.para: HOLCIM-NORTH AMERICA/DIVESTITURE (UPDATE 1, PIX)UPDATE 1-Cement maker Holcim completes $30 billion North American spin-off

news.title: TRULiV raises funds from BCCL at ₹356.50 crore valuation
news.para: The capital raised will be used to expand the company's footprint into new cities, strengthen its technology platform, and expand into hospitality sector including holiday homes and retirement living.

news.title: Institutional investments in Indian real estate set to fall 37% to $3 billion in Jan-Jun: JLL
news.para: Real estate consultant JLL India data showed that institutional investments in Indian real estate are likely to fall to USD 3.06 billion in the January-June period this year as compared to USD 4.89 billion in the year-ago period.

news.title: MO Alternates secures ₹1,050 crore from complete exits in second realty fund
news.para: The fund, with a corpus of Rs 489 crore, focused on providing structured capital to developers for mid-income residential projects across key urban markets in India. The capital was deployed in cities with significant housing demand and was aimed at supporting project completion and delivery timelines.

news.title: Embassy Developments to jointly develop 17.9 acres land in Whitefield, Bengaluru
news.para: The planned development will comprise of residential community with an estimated gross development value (GDV) of ₹1,600 crore.

news.title: Homebuyers in Bengaluru feel betrayed as builders flout RERA orders with impunity
news.para: From construction delays and refund refusals to outright defiance of Rera compensation orders, aggrieved buyers say enforcement is virtually non-existent. What began as a hopeful investment has, for many, turned into a fight for justice that drags on for years.

news.title: Pune: Kharadi residents to receive digital property cards by September 2025
news.para: The project, part of Central govt's ownership scheme launched in 2019, aims to streamline urban land management. In Pune district, it will be first implemented in Kharadi — now under the Pune Municipal Corporation (PMC) limits.

news.title: Jaipur: Tenants in Walled City’s crumbling buildings worry
news.para: When asked about this year's preparations, Pushpendra Singh Rathore, deputy commissioner of JMC-H's vigilance wing, said, "We have directed all zonal DCs to reassess and prepare a fresh list of structurally unsafe buildings."

news.title: Mumbai: BMC plan to auction prime plots stalled as two government bodies want to procure them
news.para: The move had marked the first time the civic body opted to auction its own plots, indicating a shift in its strategy to monetise real estate assets and generate long-term revenue. However, the auction process faced multiple hurdles.

news.title: HC junks Greater Noida development body order to cancel land for project
news.para: The court struck down restoration charges, time extension penalties, and penal interest imposed by GNIDA, asking the Authority to restore the plot and revalidate the project map.

news.title: New bylaws not enough to regularise hotels in residential areas in Rajasthan
news.para: The industry stated that while complying with rules of not hosting weddings and running rooftop restaurants catering to the general public is easy, the 60-foot road width criterion will create a hurdle for most hotels built decades ago in the vicinity of railways, monuments, and bus stands.

news.title: Not just land, now 7/12 documents for building floors too in Maharashtra
news.para: Bawankule said, "In Maharashtra, we do not have system of issuing 7/12 for vertical buildings. We will soon launch the Vertical 7/12 Yojna in state, so that residents on each of the floors will also get that document."

news.title: Build PMAY schemes with 1,000 flats in each of six constituencies: Maharashtra CM
news.para: CM Fadnavis congratulated the new homeowners and praised the quality of construction undertaken by NMC. "The same quality flat is being sold for Rs18 lakh in the adjacent scheme, but citizens are getting the flat under PMAY for Rs9 lakh," said Fadnavis.

news.title: Residents of Noida’s Amrapali Riverview society protest lack of amenities
news.para: "We held a protest march against NBCC and the CR office today from River View Society to the main gate of Gaur Project (Laser Park, Phase-3), in which a large number of men, women, elderly, and children participated" said Mritunjay Sharma from River View Society, Greater Noida West.

news.title: New policy may allow owners of old flats bigger homes for free in Noida
news.para: The policy, approved on June 14, offers existing homeowners larger apartments with a minimum 15% increase in carpet area along with temporary accommodation for the period when reconstruction will take place.
